
[1]prudent

   PRU'DENT, a. Cautious; circumspect; practically wise; careful of the
   consequences of enterprises, measures or actions; cautious not to act
   when the end is of doubtful utility, or probably impracticable.

   The prudent man looketh well to his going. Prov.14.

   A prudent man foreseeth the evil and hideth himself. Prov.22.

   1. Dictated or directed by prudence; as prudent behavior.

   2. Foreseeing by instinct; as the prudent crane.

   3. Frugal; economical; as a prudent woman; prudent expenditure of
   money.

   4. Wise; intelligent.
